<subSubSection id="CE8CD335D103953FBE99394B0A8573D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="studied type specimens">
<paragraph id="B5F177397B7E52F65AD219912D5E4DF7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Studied type specimens.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4C190EA5E90D68AD36CAF483B1C7C24" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Paraguay • 1 ♀, neotype of 
<taxonomicName id="8CC8AA99DFA13D5561C63F2A58571D5F" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microdon diaphanus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="9241C79743586B44065B7E2C29FC9AC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Microdon diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sack (new designation, see notes); Encarnacion; 15 Jun. 1927; Shannon &amp; Del Ponte leg.; USNM.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21E02DE870B276A0EA2181DF8040EC0F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Label 1: &quot;ex ant colony / in arboreal / bromelia&quot;; label 2: &quot;Encarnacion / Paraguay 15.6.27 / Shannon &amp; Del Ponte
<normalizedToken id="4BD13FC68008F8869D0E84128B879065" originalValue="””">&quot;&quot;</normalizedToken>
; label 3: &quot;USNMENT / [barcode] / 01371103&quot;. Coll USNM. With empty puparium mounted on same pin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5541D94F7941D89188160B7FB897CEED" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="additional specimens">
<paragraph id="C400AEB5219B38579E7E060D9A5C6238" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Additional specimens.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4134ADE73DF4D4D4D67CDDA0C2064B55" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Brazil • 1 ♀; Jundiahy; 13 Aug. 1899; NHMUK.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21EADCCD83CD58727F1FBB8EA3C6592D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Paraguay • 2 ♀; same label data as neotype; USNM.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="00D395270D24E73627FA4262FA07C0E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F3DECA14A70DB354C1CA7A215B13BE8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6C0E9A81FA91C8CD9BD74C66CBE96B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 16 mm (based on 
<bibRefCitation id="482B5A9C9948F6B113FF7F17708D1DD2" author="Sack, P" journalOrPublisher="A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B30" refString="Sack, P, 1921. Dr. L. Zuercher's Dipteran-Ausbeute aus Paraguay: Syrphiden. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 87(A): 127-149." title="Dr. L. Zuercher's Dipteran-Ausbeute aus Paraguay: Syrphiden. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 87 (A): 127 - 149." year="1921">Sack 1921</bibRefCitation>
), female 16.5-18.5. The constricted abdomen, absence of a triangle of golden pile on the mesoscutum, and partly dark wings place 
<taxonomicName id="4DBE4561C664EED53433DBB56CF481FB" genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="15C007E88EC8376F3731EBB124CD787B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a group with 
<taxonomicName id="B2A0FD687AA717BCE12325C6A857D7FA" genus="P." lsidName="P. elongatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="8A22B945FDEBCD8DDADD4A283921B21B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="167FD4B3F878C90EC8124CE83BC4D04E" genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetia">
<emphasis id="4B71D9CFBB9D154BACA6A3718AF024BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2102BC2C75B4C733FE0C89CCFD7E5B1" genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetoides">
<emphasis id="0AF4EEE62C43DC0C94CB79343A8E9E55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="397A5A3A47FE43B8EF342DA2E82A7D76" authority="Reemer, 2013" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Peradon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peradon diaphanus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="CF3C5FAB26A49423B942B32A4A59F928" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peradon diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other three species by tergite 2 being longer than wide, and also by the rufous golden pilose mesoscutum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAA362F3AFF5611001D13A32D16A6A39" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E80FA918278A3B52F9CF59480142E02B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="881F3CF52C3FB38EDE7C3628DE9F5D24" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="39C7BD7720D0E83A6CA8918628A26FB8" author="Pape, T" journalOrPublisher="Conservation Genetics" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.diptera.org/" refId="B20" refString="Pape, T, Thompson, FC, 2013. .http://www.diptera.org/" url="http://www.diptera.org/" year="2013">Pape and Thompson (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F6C2CE3684E06CC4B125845ECB36A8A2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.288.4095" author="Reemer, M" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 213" refId="B25" refString="Reemer, M, Stahls, G, 2013a. Generic revision and species classification of the Microdontinae (Diptera, Syrphidae). ZooKeys 288: 1 - 213" title="Generic revision and species classification of the Microdontinae (Diptera, Syrphidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.288.4095" volume="288" year="2013 a">
Reemer and 
<normalizedToken id="A1B09B938B570724B6A0720E1B1915C9" originalValue="Ståhls">Stahls</normalizedToken>
(2013a)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B10B4DE33FE3A5DEE2EBADC0EB7A2B36" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.49898" author="Thompson, FC" journalOrPublisher="A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 195" refId="B29" refString="Thompson, FC, Vockeroth, JR, Sedman, YS, 1976. Family Syrphidae. A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States 46: 1 - 195" title="Family Syrphidae." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.49898" volume="46" year="1976">Thompson et al. (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, the type of 
<taxonomicName id="11F197054ACB79A5C0E0B34E30FB36B3" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microdon diaphanus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="38D5DCACFD57798B410501CA9D41C899" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Microdon diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deposited in the DEI (
<normalizedToken id="36A4CEADFAE32A127409B096EB907AD6" originalValue="Müncheberg">Muencheberg</normalizedToken>
). However, attempts to find it in that collection failed (pers. comm. F. Menzel). The DEI is part of the Senckenberg research institute, which also holds entomological collections in Dresden (SNSD) and Frankfurt (SMF). Enquiries at these institutions did not result in finding the type either. As a large part of the collection of P. Sack was destroyed during World War II (
<bibRefCitation id="BBA864F46DC817F44FE30C6F512C9EAF" author="Franz, E" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B7" refString="Franz, E, 1967. Geschichte der Entomologischen Sekstion. Senckenbergiana Biologica 48(B): 55-72." title="Geschichte der Entomologischen Sekstion. Senckenbergiana Biologica 48 (B): 55 - 72." year="1967">Franz 1967</bibRefCitation>
), it seems probable that this has also happened to the type of 
<taxonomicName id="B3A34C7D6AB4070B3EFCDBE6A3C8CFC2" genus="M." lsidName="M. diaphanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis id="DFCC7ABF89B892905A850AA38BA31D17" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In order to ensure the stability of this taxon, a neotype designation is deemed desirable. One female from Brazil (coll. NHMUK) and three females from Paraguay (coll. USNM) agree well with the original description and the figure in 
<bibRefCitation id="A14F4A10B6F1C569D496E86137939AA3" author="Sack, P" journalOrPublisher="A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B30" refString="Sack, P, 1921. Dr. L. Zuercher's Dipteran-Ausbeute aus Paraguay: Syrphiden. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 87(A): 127-149." title="Dr. L. Zuercher's Dipteran-Ausbeute aus Paraguay: Syrphiden. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 87 (A): 127 - 149." year="1921">Sack (1921)</bibRefCitation>
. As the species was originally described from Paraguay, one of the Paraguayan females is here designated as neotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5920B83091970707F154B217D25DF1AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The three females from Paraguay are mounted together with empty puparia and carry labels stating &quot;ex ant colony in arboreal bromelia&quot;. This is the first known record of an association of a 
<taxonomicName id="6567122BA6E1AA35B51F09F2A17CEA87" authority="Reemer, 2013" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Peradon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peradon" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7C62EA415225AB79EAF80DF9BEEA2B9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peradon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with ants. Unfortunately, the ants remain unidentified.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F2BE0222DD1FD221774B8C37FDA39115" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CEA2089CD1E4B1FF6E083483639D6063" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A2AC51C39D6A52F8CAFEA50E74CD21B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Known from the Brazilian state 
<normalizedToken id="55CA9ECCF344649801D65DA082490B6E" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo and from Paraguay.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
